OL,3,CWhat is the Lampard mental health
OL,4,CInquiry?
OL,6,FDuring the inquiry Baroness Lampard
OL,7,Fwill hear evidence from bereaved
OL,8,Ffamilies, former patients, experts and
OL,9,Fstaff.
OL,11,FFrom this she will draw up
OL,12,Frecommendations that the government
OL,13,Fcan choose to accept or ignore.
OL,15,FThe inquiry has no power to find
OL,16,Fanyone guilty or innocent, but if
OL,17,FBaroness Lampard believes a crime has
OL,18,Ftaken place she will report this to
OL,19,Fpolice.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/21
